          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Averaged cross sections were derived from reaction",
                "rates measured, for reaction rates see formula (1) in",
                "PR/C,206,110804,2023. Difference of real spectra at",
                "the sample position and Pu-239 fission neutron spectrum",
                "was taken into account."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " For the neutron spectrum filtered by water, calculated",
                " by MCNP6.",
                " For difference of spectra for monitor reaction and",
                " reaction under study.",
                " The burnup of the reactor was not taken into the",
                " account."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Of author Martin Schulc.",
                " -The correction for neutron spectrum filtered by water",
                "was calculated by MCNP6.",
                "This approach for PFNS reconstruction is validated in",
                "an article: KOSTAL, Michal, et al. Impact of reactor",
                "neutron spectrum on measured spectrum averaged cross",
                "sections. Annals of Nuclear Energy, 2022, 179: 109418.",
                "Since the correction factor is validated, we can relate",
                "the result to 239Pu PFNS.",
                "-Response function is the cross section in group",
                "structure multiplied by the neutron flux in group",
                "structure (sum of groups then returns reaction rates).",
                "E50% is the energy where the multiplication gives 50%",
                "of reaction rate."
              ]
            }
          ],
